{"tid":2173980,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"LeBron Shames: 我地真係好驚","createTime":"2020-08-25T14:48:53.000Z","updateTime":"2020-08-25T16:27:58.000Z","uid":270889,"like":1,"dislike":13,"uniUserReply":10,"replies":[{"pid":"28f180902eb74e0f3c898587ee0b9f38f5ce585b","tid":2173980,"uid":270889,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-08-25T14:48:53.000Z","msg":"<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=raV1HUNXT-I\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DraV1HUNXT-I&d=byei43Pfdy9TlHy68xWwXUcTp%2BQsjpNju1TtMRGBB4E%3D&h=7a4f1412\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=raV1HUNXT-I</a><br />\n<br />\nJames had 30 points and 10 assists in 28 minutes before heading to the bench late in the third quarter. The Lakers led by as many as 38 points for their third straight win in the opening-round series, the team's first playoff appearance since 2013.<br />\n<br />\nAfter the game, James detailed<span class=\"red\"> the emotional burden </span>of both honoring Bryant and coping with the shooting of Jacob Blake, a Black man, by police officers in Kenosha, Wisconsin.<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;<span class=\"red\">I can&rsquo;t even enjoy a playoff win right now, which is the sad part</span>,&rdquo; he said.<br />\n<br />\nJames spoke at length about the shooting, which has sparked violent protests. Blake, who remained hospitalized on Monday, was shot, apparently in the back, as he leaned into his SUV while his three children sat in the vehicle.<br />\n<br />\n<span class=\"red\">&ldquo;We are scared as Black people in America,&rdquo; James said. &ldquo;Black men, Black women, Black kids. We are, we are terrified.&rdquo;</span><br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://twitter.com/ABC/status/1298254204218290178?s=20\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FABC%2Fstatus%2F1298254204218290178%3Fs%3D20&d=byei43Pfdy9TlHy68xWwXUcTp%2BQsjpNju1TtMRGBB4E%3D&h=d02f1291\" data-ef-url=\"http